Alembic migration scripts for the Job Visualizer backend.

env.py wires DATABASE_URL and SCRAPER_ENVIRONMENT (via
src/backend/api/config.Settings) into Alembic and uses
version_table=alembic_version_{env} so local/qa/prod tracking rows do not
collide in a shared database. target_metadata points at
src/backend/api/db_models.Base.

The baseline revision (upgrade/downgrade are no-ops) exists so prod can be
`alembic stamp <baseline>` before the first Alembic-era deploy. After stamp,
`alembic upgrade head` is a no-op against prod. See
docs/implementations/alembicMigration/DEPLOY.md for the full runbook.

Add a schema change:
  1. Edit src/backend/api/db_models.py
  2. cd src/backend && alembic revision --autogenerate -m "short message"
  3. Review the generated file — any multi-column ALTER on the same table
     must be one op.batch_alter_table(...) block, not N op.alter_column calls
     (per docs/incidents/2026-04-18-migration-filled-postgres-volume/volume-
     downgrade-playbook.md Rule 3).
  4. cd src/backend && alembic upgrade head
  5. Commit the revision file.
